Wash and dry all produce. Peel and dice @carrots{1}(peeled and diced) into small
cubes. Halve, peel, and finely chop @yellow onion{1/2}(peeled and finely chopped).
Dice @Roma tomato{1}(diced).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add
@Italian chicken sausage{9%ounce}(broken up) and cook, breaking up meat into
pieces, until browned, about ~{7%minutes}.

Add another drizzle of olive oil to pot, then stir in carrot, onion, and a large
pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, about
~{5%minutes}.

Add tomato, @garlic powder{1/4%tsp}, and half the @Tuscan heat spice{1/2%tablespoon}
to pot (use the rest of the spice as you like). Cook, stirring, until fragrant,
about ~{1%minute}. Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2} and @warm water{3 1/2%cups}
(6 cups for 4 servings), scraping up any browned bits on bottom of pot.

Add half the @gemelli pasta{3%ounce} (all for 4 servings). Cover and bring to a
boil, then immediately reduce heat to low. Simmer until pasta is al dente, about
~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place @butter{2%tablespoon} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{} and
microwave until just softened, about ~{10%seconds} (do not melt). Stir in
@Parmesan cheese{1%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{1/4%tsp}, a pinch of @salt{pinch},
and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} (save the rest of the cheese for the
next step; use the rest of the garlic powder as you like).

Halve @ciabatta bread{1}(halved) and toast in a #toaster{} or #toaster oven{}
until golden. Spread butter mixture onto cut sides of ciabatta, then halve on a
diagonal.

Stir @spinach{5%ounce} and @Parmesan cheese{2%tablespoon} into soup until spinach
has melted. Season with plenty of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Divide soup between
#bowls{}, then sprinkle with remaining Parmesan and a pinch of remaining chili
flakes if you like. Serve with toasts on the side for dipping.

> This is chicken noodle soup the way your Italian grandma would've made it. The
> fusilli pasta spirals, sweet chicken sausage, and sprinkle of Parmesan cheese
> bring that old-world charm to every bowl.